### CLUSTER

Seismos/ra'ash clusters at covenant-transition moments: Sinai (establishment), crucifixion/resurrection (transfer), Babylon's fall (judgment), Day of YHWH (consummation). But ALSO at: storms (Mat 8:24), social upheaval (Mat 21:10), military invasion (Jer 8:16, Eze 26:10), economic collapse (Eze 27:28), political overthrow (Isa 14:16, Hag 2:22), agricultural abundance (Ps 72:16), animal energy (Job 39:20).

### CONSISTENT READING

God shaking/disrupting established order — but "established order" is broader than geology. The shaking applies to any domain: ground, sea, sky, nations, kingdoms, cities, economies, temples, prisons, people's bodies. What is "shakeable" = removable/unfaithful (Heb12:27 — "removing what can be shaken so what CANNOT be shaken remains"). Opposite = ROCK. The English "earthquake" collapses this entire semantic range into one geological phenomenon and obscures 80% of the biblical usage.

### ANOMALIES

1Ki19:11 — God NOT in the shaking. Exception proves rule: shaking alone ≠ God's voice; covenant word (still small voice) follows disruption. | Ps72:16 — POSITIVE shaking: grain waving abundantly. Not all ra'ash is judgment — it can be fruitfulness. | Job39:20 — Horse leaping. Physical vitality, no covenant context. Broadest edge of the word.

### CROSS-TESTAMENT

H7493→LXX seio/seismos→NT seismos. Hag2:6 quoted Heb12:26. Direct prophetic-to-apostolic chain. Same Greek word throughout. The narrowing happened in English translation, not in the biblical languages.